For my baseline: In 2019, Gardner reported that M&A deals above 25bn take an average of 279 days to close. Investopedia also cited 6 months to multiple years to close. Court process is planned to beginn on 17 October and lasting for five days. From 22 October to 1 January around 2.25 months ~68 days or 24% of the average --> Baseline ~ 10%

The fact government accounts are no better than bots with one way communication and rarely 2 way communication with the public. Twitter valuation is much higher that what it should be. It’s virtually impossible to communicate with government employees or agencies on Twitter rendering it a useless platform for communicating with government. Generally communication with so called “followers” is sparse and useless as well. If you are not extremely popular, Twitter is a waste of time if your looking for a response. Analytical information is highly useful and shows to what extreme people avoid responding to tweets. Say for instance you tweet about UFOs to high level government agencies, you can see that there were lots of reviews but zero responses. That of course tells a person who created the tweet many things and most of them aren’t good. The main takeaway is your government is arrogant, selfish, snobby and think they are above responding to the public. You are there to serve them not the other way around. Because Twitter is one big democrat snob fest, I don’t think Elon Musk is going to purchase Twitter.
